.TH "BOB-LS-RECIPES" "1" "Jan 17, 2026" "1.2.0" "Bob"
.SH NAME
bob-ls-recipes \- List all known recipes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
bob ls\-recipes [\-h] [\-D DEFINES] [\-c CONFIGFILE]
               [\-\-sandbox | \-\-slim\-sandbox | \-\-dev\-sandbox | \-\-strict\-sandbox | \-\-no\-sandbox]
               [\-\-all | \-\-used | \-\-orphaned] [\-\-sources]
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
List known recipes. In contrast to the bob\-ls \%<#\:manpage-bob-ls> command, which works
on packages, this command works on recipes.
.sp
By default, all found recipes are printed (\fB\-\-all\fP). Because the recipe YAML
files can declare more than one recipe (see
multiPackage \%<#\:configuration-recipes-multipackage>), the number of listed recipes is
usually bigger than the number of YAML files. Add the \fB\-\-sources\fP option too
see which file declared what recipe.
.sp
Note that listing used or orphaned recipes very much depends on the project
configuration. Especially when using layers, there may be a large number of
unused recipes.
.SH OPTIONS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \fB\-\-all\fP
List all recipes (default).
.TP
.B \fB\-c CONFIGFILE\fP
Use config File
.TP
.B \fB\-\-dev\-sandbox\fP
Enable development sandboxing.
.TP
.B \fB\-D DEFINES\fP
Override default environment variable
.TP
.B \fB\-\-no\-sandbox\fP
Disable sandboxing.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-orphaned\fP
List recipes that are unused.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-sandbox\fP
Enable partial sandboxing.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-slim\-sandbox\fP
Enable slim sandboxing.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-sources\fP
Print source YAML file names. This includes the recipe and all inherited
classes. The file names are separated by TAB character.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-strict\-sandbox\fP
Enable strict sandboxing.
.TP
.B \fB\-\-used\fP
List all used recipes. These are recipes that are referenced directly or
indirectly by a root package.
